# BubbleSnapScroll

Reusable component: `BubbleSnapScroll.tsx`.

## When to use
Stacked “bubbles” (cards) that may overflow vertically; keep a **sticky header outside** this component and put only scrollable bubbles **inside** `BubbleSnapScroll`.

## Parent layout (required)
The scroll port must have a **bounded height** or it will grow with content and never scroll:
- Parent chain: `flex: 1` and `minHeight: 0` up to a fixed-height shell (e.g. station card).
- Sibling before `BubbleSnapScroll` (identity row) stays natural height; `BubbleSnapScroll` gets `flex: 1` + `minHeight: 0` via its root `styles.port`.

## Behaviour
- Measures each child bubble height (`onLayout`), builds `snapToOffsets` for native snap (where supported).
- **No system scrollbars** — matches kiosk UI; navigation uses FAB chevrons and touch scroll.
- Large circular FAB chevrons (2× base size), **horizontally aligned** with bubble info icons (`connectorIdleRfidInfoIcon`: may overlap the “i”). Optional `fabRight` overrides alignment.
- Arrow actions use `scrollTo({ animated: true })` toward the next/previous snap offset.

## Integration
Import `BubbleSnapScroll` and wrap bubble children only. Do not nest unrelated full-screen scrolls inside without testing.

## Info / help (`InfoReader`)
Single scroll block: one child `View` with inner `gap`, `fabRight={BUBBLE_SNAP_SCROLL_FAB_RIGHT_INFO}`. Scroll uses **viewport paging** when there is only one measured child (`snapOffsets.length < 2`).

## Overlays (`FullscreenOverlay`)
Enable with `bubbleSnapScroll` on `FullscreenOverlay` for screens like `Support` and `QR`, where stacked cards may overflow. Same FAB inset as Pomoc; body uses `overlayCard` / `overlayScrollContent` styles.
